translated: Hörby, Malmöhus County, son of principal G. A. Hallbeck and Ida Nilsson. Married in 1936 to Anna-Lisa Börjesson, with two children: Lena, born in 1940, and Kerstin, born in 1945. He took his high school degree in Lund in 1927, a bachelor's degree in Lund in 1932, and spent a trial year in Stockholm in 1938. He traveled to Germany in 1932-1933, 1937, 1938, and 1939, and to England in 1938. He was a substitute lecturer at the University of Marburg from 1932-1933, a part-time teacher at Tomelilla Siamrealskola and folkhögskola from 1934-1935, a teacher in Falkenberg from 1935-1937, an assistant teacher there from 1939-1940, and an ordinary subject teacher in Swedish and German in Lilla Edet from 1939.
